reviews.review_text:
music isnt crisp but the aud is.


still dig recordings (like this) with the energy/crowd 

 to its better than the SBD one.

Can't listen While the playing may be spectacular for all I know, the fact that the band's sound is buried by the recording makes it too hard to listen. Also, the set list offers nothing interesting if you have heard any of the rest of the tour. 

I often like audience recordings, and haven't heard this show's SBD, but if it's really worse than this, it would have to be REAL bad. More recent AUDs than this one (there are 2 at this point) are even worse: this one at least has the benefit of not being muddy on the high end. Since you still can't hear Garcia that often, though, look elsewhere for a good time.
